    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-22T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-22T12:00:00-05:00" n="444"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d444">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/333: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MEV1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-22T14:00:00-03:00"
                            >August 22, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>90, Department’s 65, August 20, 2 p.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d444fn3">Not
                        printed.</note> The proclamation by <persName corresp="#p_GMGPA1">General
                        Gões Monteiro</persName> dated August 2nd states that inasmuch as the
                    manufacture of arms, munitions and other war material is a monopoly of the
                    Federal Government, violators of the law will be energetically dealt with.
                    Factories of such materials whether belonging to nationals or foreigners will be
                    destroyed and the properties confiscated and the persons involved will be held
                    criminally liable. Those who aid the rebels or interfere with the Federal
                    operations likewise will be held criminally liable as will those who by means of
                    the radio or printed word incite or practice action against the Federal or State
                    Governments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MEV1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
